The City of Cape Town is expected to lower water restrictions from Level 5 to Level 3 from December 1, it has announced. This means that Capetonians will be able to use 105 litres a day, each – up from 70 litres a day, Mayor Dan Plato said. Tariffs will also be lowered. If residents use less than 6 000 litres per month, they can expect to pay 35.5% less. Information on reduced water and sanitation tariffs can be found 
here and frequently asked questions about Level 3 restrictions can be found here. Here are the guidelines that the City has provided for Level 3 water usage: